@@ -0,0 +1,20 @@
+# FocusedEditableTextReplaceTextEdit Object
+
+* `kind` string - Can be `replaceText`.
+* `text` string - The replacement text.
+* `start` number (optional) - UTF-16 start offset of the replacement range in
+  the full focused editable text. If `end` is provided and `start` is omitted,
+  the range starts at `0`.
+* `end` number (optional) - UTF-16 end offset of the replacement range in the
+  full focused editable text. If `start` is provided and `end` is omitted, the
+  range ends at the current text length.
+* `selectionAfter` [FocusedEditableTextEditSelection](focused-editable-text-edit-selection.md) (optional) -
+  Best-effort selection to apply after the edit. The range is interpreted as
+  UTF-16 offsets in the final focused editable text and is clamped to the final
+  text length.
+
+When both `start` and `end` are omitted, Electron replaces the current selection
+or active composition. Replacement ranges outside the current focused editable
+text are rejected.
+
+This object is passed to `webContents.editFocusedEditableText()`.
