+#### `contents.editFocusedEditableText(edit)` _Experimental_
+
+* `edit` [FocusedEditableTextInsertTextEdit](structures/focused-editable-text-insert-text-edit.md) | [FocusedEditableTextReplaceTextEdit](structures/focused-editable-text-replace-text-edit.md)
+
+Returns `Promise<FocusedEditableText | null>` - resolves with the focused
+editable text snapshot after the edit is applied, or `null` if no focused
+editable text can be edited.
+
+Edits the currently focused editable text using Chromium's text input path.
+`insertText` inserts into the current selection or active composition.
+`replaceText` replaces the requested UTF-16 range, or the current selection when
+no range is provided.
+
+`start`, `end`, and `selectionAfter` offsets are UTF-16 offsets in the full
+focused editable text. For `replaceText`, omitting `start` means the beginning
+of the text, omitting `end` means the end of the text, and omitting both means
+the current selection. Replacement ranges outside the current text are rejected.
+
+`selectionAfter` is best-effort. If provided, Electron clamps it to the final
+text length and applies it after the edit. If selection placement cannot be
+completed, the edit itself is not rolled back. The returned
+[`FocusedEditableText`](structures/focused-editable-text.md) contains the
+actual final selection.
+
+Password inputs return `null`. Custom editors backed by DOM-editable content are
+handled on a best-effort basis. Editors backed by canvas, virtual documents, or
+application-internal models may only expose the focused DOM control.
+
 #### `contents.isLoading()`
 
 Returns `boolean` - Whether web page is still loading resources.
